<Author>Lilly12103
<Content>So bad we left and asked for our money back. Where do I even begin... I booked a room at this hotel blindly because my plans changed and I needed a place to stay. It was inexpensive, and my husband and I figured How bad could it be? Yes, it can be that bad. The room was worse than a prison cell. At least in prison they can hang up photos. The walls were various shades of beige, grime, and mold. And completely bare. There was a bed in the middle of the room and nothing else. The windows were broken. The bathroom was last updated 50 years ago, and I was afraid to take my shoes off in the room. We had to wait for the cleaning lady to finish before she let us in the room, and I saw only towels in the laundry basket and no sheets, so I'm not entirely sure they change the sheets after each visitor. There was a random door opening up to a balcony that looked over the nasty, noisy street below. I wouldn't recommend this place to my worst enemy. We left and found another place to stay in Esperanza, which even though it cost us twice as much at least we didn't inhale too much of whatever mold was growing on the ceiling. The only bonus was leaving- they gave us all our money back. Words cannot express how bad this place was. 
